data.name: Uroktor Scale+
data.description: A high-quality Uroktor scale. Heat-resistant, bright crimson, and popular with the ladies.

data.name: Rachnoid Silk
data.description: Silk shot by Rachnoid. Its high tensile strength makes it stronger than it looks.

data.name: Rachnoid Silk+
data.description: High quality silk that is nearly as strong as rope and more flexible too.

data.name: Bnahabra Shell
data.description: Just as useful as sturdy wyvern shell in the hands of a clever craftsman.

data.name: Bnahabra Carapace
data.description: The hardest part of the shell. Reveals curious properties when forged.

data.name: Bnahabra Wing
data.description: Difficult to forge with— the results vary depending on which surface you use.

data.name: Bnahabra Stinger
data.description: A Bnahabra stinger. It's actually a hollow tube that houses paralytic secretions.

data.name: Altaroth Jaw
data.description: Removing these mouthparts requires a deft hand.

data.name: Altaroth Stomach
data.description: A transparent sac cut from an Altaroth's abdomen, used to store who knows what.

data.name: Quality Stomach
data.description: A high-quality sac from an Altaroth's abdomen. It's thin, but durable.

data.name: Gajau Skin
data.description: Gajau skin known for its slimy mucus layer. Highly water-resistant.

data.name: Gajau Scale
data.description: High-quality Gajau skin. Thick and hard to work with, but it's worth the effort.

data.name: Gajau Whisker
data.description: Gajau whiskers often used in aquatic gear as they resist water.

data.name: Gajau Whisker+
data.description: High-quality Gajau whiskers. They're so girthy, you could use them for fishing line.

data.name: Remobra Hide
data.description: A glossy and subdued black hide taken from a Remobra.

data.name: Remobra Hide+
data.description: A lustrous and elegant black hide taken from a Remobra.

data.name: Striped Hide
data.description: Unassuming black-and-red hues from a Remobra that some hunters swear by.

data.name: Remobra Head
data.description: The snake-like head of a Remobra. It still looks ready to pounce!

data.name: Izuchi Pelt
data.description: Izuchi hair. Very versatile— you can't go five steps without seeing it somewhere.

data.name: Izuchi Pelt+
data.description: High-quality hair taken from an elite Izuchi in the pack. Pleasantly soft to touch.

data.name: Izuchi Tail
data.description: Izuchi that swing their tail skillfully may become the leader of the pack.

data.name: Wroggi Scale
data.description: A scale from a Wroggi. Its vivid color warns predators of its venomous properties.

data.name: Wroggi Scale+
data.description: A quality Wroggi scale. The thickness shows this Wroggi lived a long life.

data.name: Wroggi Hide
data.description: Hide from a Wroggi. You could make some really nice orange leather with this.

data.name: Baggi Scale
data.description: A scale from a Baggi. A little tougher than a Jaggi scale.

data.name: Baggi Scale+
data.description: A quality scale taken from a Baggi. Important for strengthening weapons.

data.name: Baggi Hide
data.description: Smooth hide from under a Baggi's scales. Perfect for life in tough environments.

data.name: Jaggi Scale
data.description: A scale carved from a Jaggi. Popular among hunters for its beauty and versatility.

data.name: Jaggi Scale+
data.description: A vividly-colored superior Jaggi scale that can be used to make hardier equipment.

data.name: Jaggi Hide
data.description: Hide from under a Jaggi's scales. Cheap, easy to work with, and has numerous uses.

data.name: Jaggi Hide+
data.description: A quality Jaggi hide with a variety of uses. Popular for its beautiful hue.

data.name: Great Izuchi Pelt
data.description: Hair that grows on an Izuchi's neck and head. Fades from white to orange.

data.name: Great Izuchi Pelt+
data.description: Great Izuchi hair. On top of being gorgeous, it's smooth as a gentle breeze.

data.name: Great Izuchi Hide
data.description: This hide of a mature Izuchi is a deep orange fitting for the leader of the herd.

data.name: Great Izuchi Hide+
data.description: Great Izuchi hide. It's lightweight, strong, and vivid—always a hot item.

data.name: Great Izuchi Tail
data.description: A crescent-bladed tail. A flick of the herd leader's tail brings its prey down.

data.name: Great Izuchi Tail+
data.description: Crescent-bladed tail. Its edge has been honed by the wind to be razor sharp.

data.name: Great Baggi Hide
data.description: Hide from a Great Baggi. Despite how tough it is, it's covered in old scars.

data.name: Great Baggi Hide+
data.description: Quality Great Baggi hide. You'd be hard pressed to hurt a Baggi this tough.

data.name: Great Baggi Claw
data.description: A robust Great Baggi claw. It's thicker than a regular old Baggi claw.

data.name: Great Baggi Claw+
data.description: A quality Great Baggi Claw. Sharpened by battle, it's perfect for weapons.

data.name: King's Crest
data.description: A token of an alpha Baggi. The bigger the crest, the stronger they are.

data.name: Kulu-Ya-Ku Scale
data.description: With some fine crafting, the milky white color of these scales can be improved.

data.name: Kulu-Ya-Ku Scale+
data.description: Boasts brilliant coloration, and leaves nothing to be desired in strength.

data.name: Kulu-Ya-Ku Hide
data.description: Due to its versatile coloration, this hide is often used in clothing.

data.name: Kulu-Ya-Ku Hide+
data.description: Just like the sturdy Kulu hide you know, except stronger, and smoother too.

data.name: Kulu-Ya-Ku Beak
data.description: This beak, developed to eat the yolks out of eggs, has a peculiar shape.

data.name: Kulu-Ya-Ku Beak+
data.description: This Kulu beak is a peck above the rest. Stronger than typical wyvern hide.

data.name: Kulu-Ya-Ku Plume
data.description: These feathers are a hit among trendy youth for their vibrant patterns.

data.name: Kulu-Ya-Ku Plume+
data.description: These larger, more colorful feathers are often used in decorative items.

data.name: Great Wroggi Hide
data.description: Hide from a Great Wroggi. The white-on-orange pattern almost looks dyed.

data.name: Great Wroggi Hide+
data.description: Quality Great Wroggi hide. The colors would look great on an expert's weapon.

data.name: Great Wroggi Brace
data.description: A brace from a Great Wroggi. Covered in scales, it also includes claws and plate.

data.name: Great Wroggi Brace+
data.description: A tough Great Wroggi brace comprised of high-quality plate and claws.

data.name: King's Beak
data.description: A beak from a Great Wroggi. Careful with it— it's still poisonous!

data.name: Arzuros Pelt
data.description: An Arzuros pelt. The white portion is soft, while the blue is short and taut.

data.name: Arzuros Pelt+
data.description: A splendid Arzuros pelt. Sturdy enough to survive in harsh mountainous terrain.

data.name: Arzuros Shell
data.description: Shell from an Arzuros's head or back. Bends willingly and is easy to forge.

data.name: Arzuros Carapace
data.description: A quality Arzuros carapace. The thick shell can endure bites from ordinary fangs.

data.name: Arzuros Brace
data.description: A brace from an Arzuros's forelegs. Its sharp points give forged equipment a wild flavor.

data.name: Arzuros Brace+
data.description: A strong Arzuros brace. Its thorn-like protrusions make paw swipes deadly.

data.name: Lagombi Pelt
data.description: A white pelt carved from a Lagombi. One pat and you'll be hooked on its fluffy fur.

data.name: Lagombi Pelt+
data.description: Quality white Lagombi pelt. Its frosty shine makes it a sought-after luxury item.

data.name: Lagombi Ear
data.description: The long ear of a Lagombi. A lifetime in the cold has made it hard as a shell.

data.name: Lagombi Ear+
data.description: An impressive Lagombi ear. Highly developed, it can be sharp as steel if polished.

data.name: Lagombi Plastron
data.description: Shell piece from a Lagombi's belly. Its ridges allow the Lagombi to slide on ice.

data.name: Lagombi Plastron+
data.description: A strong, sticky, and thick Lagombi Plastron. Used to make superior equipment.

data.name: Lagombi Iceclaw
data.description: A Lagombi claw that's cold to the touch. Permanently covered in ice.

data.name: Lagombi Frozenclaw
data.description: A Lagombi claw surrounded by cold air. Wounds it causes freeze over in an instant.

data.name: Volvidon Shell
data.description: The heat-resistant shell of a Volvidon. Unaffected even by boiling lava.

data.name: Volvidon Carapace
data.description: A thick Volvidon carapace. The elasticity means forging it requires severe pressure.

data.name: Volvidon Claw
data.description: A claw from a Volvidon's foreleg. Dramatically raises the power of a wide swing.

data.name: Volvidon Claw+
data.description: A hard, sharp Volvidon claw. Constant exposure to heat has tempered it like steel.

data.name: Volvidon Rickrack
data.description: The jagged shell of a Volvidon's back. Its high elasticity makes it ideal for crafting flexible gear.

data.name: Aknosom Scale
data.description: An Aknosom scale that glows with a stunning ivory light. A popular material.

data.name: Aknosom Scale+
data.description: Armor woven from these beautiful white scales is in demand among royal guards.

data.name: Aknosom Feather
data.description: Feathered Aknosom scale treasured for its use in umbrellas. Sturdy yet light.

data.name: Aknosom Feather+
data.description: Quality Aknosom feather. Swing it like a blade or layer it into a shield.

data.name: Aknosom Crest
data.description: An Aknosom comb. The eyeball motif on the forehead shows up in many a ghost story.

data.name: Aknosom Crest+
data.description: Giant and flashy, this Aknosom comb looks like an elegant decorative fan.

data.name: Aknosom Beak
data.description: Aknosom beak that appears to be wearing lipstick. Used in arts and crafts.

data.name: Spongy Hide
data.description: Spongin from a Royal Ludroth's mane. Valued for its elasticity and high water retention.

data.name: Spongy Hide+
data.description: High-grade elastic hide that boasts a remarkable ability to retain water.

data.name: Royal Ludroth Scale
data.description: A small scale that enables graceful movement. You need several to forge equipment.

data.name: Royal Ludroth Scale+
data.description: A large, strong scale from a Royal Ludroth. It reflects light in every direction.

data.name: Royal Ludroth Claw
data.description: A claw from a Royal Ludroth. Adapted better to movement than to attacking.

data.name: Royal Ludroth Claw+
data.description: A sharp, pointed Royal Ludroth claw. It plunges deep into the earth with each step taken.

data.name: Royal Ludroth Crest
data.description: These crests become rigid when the beast is angry; quantity indicates status.

data.name: Royal Ludroth Crest+
data.description: A proud, strong crest befitting a pack leader. Its sharp horns shine magnificently.

data.name: Royal Ludroth Tail
data.description: The finned tail of a Royal Ludroth, used by fishermen for their boats.

data.name: Barroth Shell
data.description: Shell from a Barroth. It's pretty muddy, but that's why it's so strong.

data.name: Barroth Carapace
data.description: A Barroth's carapace coated in multiple layers of mud, making it quite rigid.

data.name: Barroth Ridge
data.description: Plate taken from a Barroth's back. Fairly rare, but makes for quality material.

data.name: Barroth Ridge+
data.description: A thick, sturdy part of a Barroth backplate. Mud and sunlight have helped to harden it further.

data.name: Barroth Claw
data.description: A Barroth claw. It's not too sharp, but can be used to strengthen many things.

data.name: Barroth Claw+
data.description: A polished claw sharpened by sand and dirt. It can dig through even the toughest earth.

data.name: Barroth Scalp
data.description: This durable part of a Barroth's skull is also the hardest to remove.

data.name: Barroth Tail
data.description: Barroth tails aren't very valuable, but the meat is hailed as a delicacy.

data.name: Fertile Mud
data.description: Mud that Barroth roll around in. Nutrient-rich and great for farming.

data.name: Rich Mud
data.description: Highly nutritious mud. While it makes great fertilizer, it works for weapons too!

data.name: Flabby Hide
data.description: Now useable as a material thanks to recent advances. Has mysterious properties.

data.name: Pearl Hide
data.description: The hide of a Khezu. Its strange properties are still not fully understood.

data.name: Suspicious Fang
data.description: These fangs are popular with occult fans and sold on the black market as cursed items.

data.name: Suspicious Fang+
data.description: Having slurped up mounds of flesh, these fangs are used in certain rituals.

data.name: Pale Bone
data.description: The rib bone from a Khezu. Still has chunks of meat attached.

data.name: Pale Steak
data.description: Fatty meat from a Khezu. Looks tasty, but cannot be eaten.

data.name: Tetranadon Hide
data.description: Made from Tetranadon belly, it's very stretchy. Now you can eat as much as you want!

data.name: Tetranadon Hide+
data.description: A life of constant combat has made this belly skin sturdy and stretchy as well.

data.name: Tetra Carapace
data.description: This shell's mossy surface acts as a cushion, making it sturdier than it looks.

data.name: Tetra Carapace+
data.description: Carapace stout enough to send any back-attacking predators packing.

data.name: Tetranadon Beak
data.description: You can store up water in this Tetranadon beak. Great for gear that uses water.

data.name: Tetranadon Beak+
data.description: This Tetranadon beak can shoot water at high pressure due to a refined structure.

data.name: Tetranadon Disc
data.description: Disc-shaped bone that protects a Tetranadon's moisturizing organ from foes.

data.name: Tetranadon Disc+
data.description: Unscathed, this disc-shaped head bone can fetch a high price as a luxury plate.

data.name: Bishaten Fur
data.description: Thick fur from around a Bishaten's neck. Protects its neck from hungry jaws.

data.name: Bishaten Fur+
data.description: Quality Bishaten fur that stays orderly under vigorous treatment. High utility.

data.name: Bishaten Talon
data.description: Bishaten claws may be small, but don't be fooled—they'll tear you to shreds.

data.name: Bishaten Talon+
data.description: These claws are a good omen for those who see the beast as a servant of the gods.

data.name: Bishaten Feather
data.description: These feathers let Bishaten go wild, providing stability while on their hind legs.

data.name: Bishaten Feather+
data.description: High-quality Bishaten feather. Light blue plumage traces the beast's wild movements.

data.name: Bishaten Horn
data.description: Bishaten horn resembling a monk's hat. Wearing it makes you smarter, supposedly.

data.name: Bishaten Horn+
data.description: Bishaten horn resembling a monk's hat. The bigger the horn, the slyer the beast.

data.name: Bisha Tailcase
data.description: Tail carapace that is super hard. Can be swung around like a ball on a chain.

data.name: Bishaten Tailcase+
data.description: Robust tail carapace that is so hard, it can even break through rocks.

data.name: Pukei-Pukei Scale
data.description: Many a hunter has been charmed by the deep forest- green hue of these scales.

data.name: Pukei-Pukei Scale+
data.description: Light and sturdy. With a little work, this could let you blend into the woods.

data.name: Pukei-Pukei Shell
data.description: The shade of green varies slightly depending on where it was harvested from.

data.name: Pukei-Pukei Carapace
data.description: The surface of this carapace is exceptionally hard; great for making armor.

data.name: Pukei-Pukei Quill
data.description: Green feather taken from a Pukei-Pukei wing. Has many decorative uses.

data.name: Pukei-Pukei Wing
data.description: This wing membrane is highly elastic and resistant to poison, giving it many uses.

data.name: Pukei-Pukei Sac
data.description: A Pukei-Pukei dewlap. Holds a digestive poison that dissolves plants.

data.name: Pukei-Pukei Sac+
data.description: Large dewlap that amps up poison production and potency by a large margin.

data.name: Pukei-Pukei Tail
data.description: The striped pattern isn't everyone's cup of tea, but some hunters dig it.

data.name: Jyuratodus Scale+
data.description: Mud sticks to this scale, building up and increasing its thickness over time.

data.name: Jyuratodus Carapace
data.description: Sturdy mud-caked Jyuratodus carapace. The mud layer boosts defense greatly.

data.name: Jyuratodus Fang+
data.description: Once this fang gets a hold of you, it wont let go until you're drowning in mud.

data.name: Jyuratodus Fin+
data.description: Using this flexible fin, the Jyuratodus is able to easily glide through the mud.

data.name: Basarios Shell
data.description: Rock-hard Basarios shell. Can be used to refine metals.

data.name: Basarios Carapace
data.description: A rigid Basarios shell. The amount of ore in it makes it closer to rock than shell.

data.name: Basarios Pleura
data.description: The shell that covers a Basarios' torso. Relatively thin and easy to manipulate.

data.name: Basarios Pleura+
data.description: The rigid shell that covers a Basarios' torso. Still thin but far denser than usual.

data.name: Basarios Wing
data.description: The wing of a Basarios. Very hard to work as a material.

data.name: Basarios Tail
data.description: A stubby Basarios tail composed of minerals more durable than ore.

data.name: Basarios Tears
data.description: Faintly pink gems found near the tear ducts of a Basarios.

data.name: Somnacanth Scale
data.description: Somnacanth scale that glistens a brilliant yellow due to its watery coating.

data.name: Somnacanth Scale+
data.description: Quality Somnacanth scale that shimmers a brilliant gold under moonlight.

data.name: Somnacanth Shell
data.description: A spiked Somnacanth carapace built for protection and cutting through water.

data.name: Somnacanth Shell+
data.description: This robust carapace lures in victims with its beauty and ruthlessly crushes them.

data.name: Somnacanth Claw
data.description: A claw with a long, hooked shape that's great for weapons, but also farm work!

data.name: Somnacanth Claw+
data.description: Somnacanth's well-developed claw. So sharp and tough that it'll easily tear through prey like butter.

data.name: Somnacanth Fin
data.description: A Somnacanth head-fin. As beautiful as the midnight sea. Careful with the barbs!

data.name: Somnacanth Fin+
data.description: In legends, these fins were thought to be the souls of those who had died at sea.

data.name: Somnacanth Dust
data.description: A glimmering blue powder shot from a Somnacanth's neck. Makes you feel sleepy.

data.name: Somnacanth Sedative
data.description: Shimmers like the falling tears of a weeping maiden, ushering in a deep sleep.

data.name: Rathian Scale
data.description: Scales of a Rathian. Their dark emerald hue exudes a feminine grace.

data.name: Rathian Scale+
data.description: A superior Rathian scale. Looks like a normal Rathian scale, but is much harder.

data.name: Rathian Shell
data.description: A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.

data.name: Rathian Carapace
data.description: Rathian shell prized for its lavish green coloration. An excellent armor material.

data.name: Rathian Webbing
data.description: This heat-resistant material is often used as armor lining.

data.name: Rathian Spike
data.description: Needle-like hair found on a Rathian's back and wings. They contain poison.

data.name: Rathian Spike+
data.description: As sharp as the keenest blade. It is longer and sturdier than other spikes.

data.name: Rathian Plate
data.description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.

data.name: Rathian Ruby
data.description: A rare, precious gem from inside a wyvern. Almost too nice to use.

data.name: Rath Wingtalon
data.description: Claws that are moderately difficult to work with. A blacksmith's first test.

data.name: Rath Wingtalon+
data.description: Razor-sharp wing talons. Could slice through a tree trunk with ease.

data.name: Rath Marrow
data.description: Recent advances allow this marrow to be extracted. It ignites on air contact.

data.name: Rath Medulla
data.description: Only recently extractable due to advances in carving techniques. Hard to forge.

data.name: Barioth Shell
data.description: White shell from a Barioth. It's strong yet incredibly light.

data.name: Barioth Carapace
data.description: A Barioth carapace with an impressive shine. Strongly resembles an ice floe.

data.name: Barioth Pelt
data.description: A white pelt that's soft to the touch. Absorbs impact almost as well as a Barioth.

data.name: Barioth Pelt+
data.description: A high-quality white pelt with a lovely texture. Nobles use it as a symbol of authority.

data.name: Barioth Claw
data.description: A deceptively sharp Barioth claw that can carve through thick glaciers.

data.name: Barioth Claw+
data.description: A claw honed in the harsh Tundra environment. It can take down prey with a single swipe.

data.name: Barioth Spike
data.description: These come in many sizes, and assist the Barioth in clinging to walls of ice.

data.name: Barioth Tail
data.description: Barioth tails are covered in hard plate, and surprisingly tough to sever.

data.name: Amber Fang
data.description: A fang from a Barioth. Can be used for weapons, but also for decoration.

data.name: Amber Fang+
data.description: Amber tusks sharpened by countless kills. Can smash through gigantic ice blocks.

data.name: Tobi-Kadachi Scale
data.description: A Tobi-Kadachi scale. Armor made from these is shockingly light.

data.name: Tobi-Kadachi Scale+
data.description: A quality scale that is flexible as a feather, and light as the wind.

data.name: Tobi-Kadachi Pelt
data.description: Prone to generating static electricity—its hairs are constantly on end.

data.name: Tobi-Kadachi Pelt+
data.description: The bolt-upright hairs are an indication of the strong electricity flowing inside.

data.name: Tobi-Kadachi Membrane
data.description: A film that is thin enough to see through, but strong enough to catch the wind.

data.name: Tobi-Kadachi Claw
data.description: These sharp-hooked Tobi- Kadachi claws are perfect for zipping up trees.

data.name: Tobi-Kadachi Claw+
data.description: Tobi-Kadachi use these razor-sharp claws to move around in the trees.

data.name: Tobi-Kadachi Electrode
data.description: Spikes made of a highly conductive material. Great for gear using electricity.

data.name: Tobi-Kadachi Electrode+
data.description: Conductive electrode that builds up and unleashes purple bolts of electricity.

data.name: Magnamalo Scale
data.description: Sturdy and small Magnamalo scale that is flexible and resistant to fangs.

data.name: Magnamalo Scale+
data.description: Glows a piercing purple, imbued with the beast's infinite fighting spirit.

data.name: Magnamalo Shell
data.description: An armor-like carapace from Magnamalo. Won't budge to any run-of-the-mill strikes.

data.name: Magnamalo Shell+
data.description: Carapace hardened by malice. So sturdy, it won't buckle to any attack.

data.name: Magnamalo Blade
data.description: A claw that has grown into a blade shape on Magnamalo's forearm. Already very sharp.

data.name: Magnamalo Blade+
data.description: Honed by blood, these arm blades cut prey in two with a single swipe.

data.name: Magnamalo Scute
data.description: Bladed hide of Magnamalo's back. Its edge is nicked from countless battles.

data.name: Magnamalo Scute+
data.description: The blades produced from Magnamalo's back when enraged show its tenacity.

data.name: Magnamalo Horn
data.description: Majestic Magnamalo horn that echoes with the sorrow of warriors slain.

data.name: Magnamalo Horn+
data.description: Horns resembling a general's helmet. Said to grow as one feasts on the defeated.

data.name: Magnamalo Tail
data.description: Magnamalo's bladed tail. Used to pierce through the guts of unsuspecting prey.

data.name: Magna Ghostprism
data.description: A gaseous crystal that emits flammable gas resembling dancing purple flames.

data.name: Magna Soulprism
data.description: A crystal of condensed gas. Its quiet exterior belies its savage explosive power.

data.name: Magnamalo Plate
data.description: Rare Magnamalo scale. Glows with a deep purple, all-consuming menace.

data.name: Purple Magna Orb
data.description: This jewel glows a sinister purple as though holding many unfortunate souls.

data.name: Anjanath Scale
data.description: Tempered by the heat of an Anjanath, this scale repels any ordinary blade.

data.name: Anjanath Scale+
data.description: Constantly subjected to forge temperatures, these scales are as hard as iron.

data.name: Anjanath Pelt
data.description: This Anjanath fur is used by local firefighters for its fire-resistant properties.

data.name: Anjanath Pelt+
data.description: Quality pelt treated as a luxury item for its stoutness and healthy coat.

data.name: Anjanath Fang
data.description: Fang shaped by the extreme pressure and heat of an Anjanath's mouth.

data.name: Anjanath Fang+
data.description: Fang of a particularly vicious Anjanath. Tears through any and all prey.

data.name: Anjanath Nosebone
data.description: Nasal bone of an Anjanath. Its characteristic structure is a hot research topic.

data.name: Anjanath Nosebone+
data.description: Nasal bones only grow to be this large in beasts that survive countless battles.

data.name: Anjanath Tail
data.description: This Anjanath tail can be used in weapons, but it's also a local delicacy.

data.name: Anjanath Plate
data.description: Rare, roiled Anjanath plating, produced by the beast's persistent rage.

data.name: Anjanath Gem
data.description: Rare jewel from within an Anjanath. Tinged with fire, it shines gallantly.

data.name: Nargacuga Scale
data.description: A scale from a Nargacuga. The surface is covered with the beast's black fur.

data.name: Nargacuga Scale+
data.description: A black Nargacuga scale. Despite its hardness, it's surprisingly light and smooth.

data.name: Nargacuga Blackfur
data.description: Black fur that grows on scales. Covers the animal in jet-black darkness.

data.name: Nargacuga Pelt+
data.description: Pitch-black fur from a Nargacuga. It absorbs light and emits pure darkness.

data.name: Nargacuga Tail
data.description: A Nargacuga's impressive tail. Might be mistaken for a weapon if seen out of context.

data.name: Narga Tailspike
data.description: A spiky scale from a Nargacuga tail. It stands up when the beast is enraged.

data.name: Nargacuga Cutwing
data.description: Blade-like Nargacuga wing. Evolved to cut down prey on the fly.

data.name: Narga Razor
data.description: The large, sharp bladewing of a Nargacuga. It can slice through foes in a flash.

data.name: Nargacuga Fang
data.description: Although small, the jagged placement of these fangs aids their cutting ability.

data.name: Nargacuga Fang+
data.description: A Nargacuga's terribly sharp fang. Evolved to tear rather than chew.

data.name: Nargacuga Marrow
data.description: Marrow as nimble as the Nargacuga itself; requires talent to properly harvest.

data.name: Narga Medulla
data.description: A Nargacuga's medulla. Merely touching it causes extreme pain, making crafting quite difficult.

data.name: Mizutsune Scale
data.description: A transparent Mizutsune scale. Its irregular shape refracts light into many bright colors.

data.name: Mizutsune Scale+
data.description: A quality Mizutsune scale. Older scales polished over time can be very valuable.

data.name: Mizutsune Purplefur
data.description: The purple fur of a Mizutsune. Stiff, but is soft as silk when soaked with bubblefoam.

data.name: Mizutsune Purplefur+
data.description: High-quality purple fur. More foam-absorbent than its lighter counterpart.

data.name: Mizutsune Claw
data.description: A claw that flies freely through bubblefoam, allowing it to be used as a spike.

data.name: Mizutsune Claw+
data.description: Friction-reducing bubblefoam helps this deadly claw slice through prey like sushi.

data.name: Mizutsune Fin
data.description: A beautiful brocade-like fin. Males have large fins that turn red to match their mood.

data.name: Mizutsune Fin+
data.description: A high-quality fin. Bubble- foam gives it an elegant pattern prettier than dye.

data.name: Mizutsune Tail
data.description: A flowing Mizutsune tail. It's prized for its supple fur and beautiful scales.

data.name: Bubblefoam
data.description: Fluid secreted by Mizutsune. Just a few drops can turn a swamp into a bubble bath.

data.name: Bubblefoam+
data.description: The top layer of Mizutsune fluid. Removes impurities and is used in many rituals.

data.name: Mizutsune Plate
data.description: An ancient scale as old as its former owner. Can even create rainbows from light.

data.name: Mizutsune Water Orb
data.description: A multicolored orb formed from a crystalized Mizutsune scale and bubblefoam.

data.name: Goss Harag Fur
data.description: This Goss hair repels snow and keeps heat in, making it popular for winter wear.

data.name: Goss Harag Fur+
data.description: Goss hair is fought over in snowy lands for its warming and protective qualities.

data.name: Goss Harag Hide
data.description: The Goss Harag's warm body and the cold outside air have tempered this hide.

data.name: Goss Harag Hide+
data.description: Freezing air and boiling Goss blood have made this skin harder than most armor.

data.name: Goss Harag Claw
data.description: Goss Harag claws. They grow not only from its toes, but also all over its feet!

data.name: Goss Harag Claw+
data.description: These rough claws have stomped through ice and slashed countless beasts.

data.name: Goss Harag Brace
data.description: Ice and snow have built up on this arm carapace until it could work as a weapon.

data.name: Goss Harag Brace+
data.description: Arm carapace thickened by the reckless behavior of a Goss Harag.

data.name: Goss Harag Horn
data.description: Lumpy blue horns of a Goss Harag. For some reason, they tend to scare children.

data.name: Goss Harag Horn+
data.description: These horns are sometimes seen as bad luck due to their demonic shape.

data.name: Block of Ice
data.description: The Goss Harag melts snow on its body, forming this ice clump on its legs at will.

data.name: Block of Ice+
data.description: Any blade or gauntlet made from this ice is sure to freeze children in terror.

data.name: Goss Harag Bile
data.description: A Goss Harag gallbladder once prized as a panacea. Good luck getting it out...

data.name: Rathalos Scale
data.description: A Rathalos scale. Wyvern scales like this one are fundamental materials.

data.name: Rathalos Scale+
data.description: An extraordinarily durable scale carved from the body of a Rathalos.

data.name: Rathalos Shell
data.description: A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.

data.name: Rathalos Carapace
data.description: This Rathalos shell emanates a nobility befitting the ruler of the skies.

data.name: Rathalos Webbing
data.description: This heat-resistant material is often used as armor lining.

data.name: Rathalos Wing
data.description: A wing from a Rathalos. Skilled artisans can craft it into strong equipment.

data.name: Rathalos Tail
data.description: A severed Rathalos tail. It has any number of uses.

data.name: Rathalos Plate
data.description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.

data.name: Rathalos Ruby
data.description: A rare, precious gem from inside a wyvern. Almost too nice to use.

data.name: Almudron Scale
data.description: Highly water-repellent Almudron scale. Allows for unhindered bog traversal.

data.name: Almudron Scale+
data.description: A quality Almudron scale. Polished by mud over many years, it's a work of art.

data.name: Almudron Shell
data.description: Overlapping scales fused with mud and Almudron mucus to form an outer shell.

data.name: Almudron Shell+
data.description: You could make a shield from the many hardened layers of bodily fluid and mud alone.

data.name: Almudron Claw
data.description: Almudron claws that excel at speedy digging. Dirt fears them.

data.name: Almudron Claw+
data.description: Sharp Almudron claw that tears through earth like water.

data.name: Almudron Fin
data.description: Red tuft of Almudron hair. Covered in a viscous fluid secreted from its pores.

data.name: Almudron Fin+
data.description: Fin-like tuft of hair that causes mud waves and whirlpools with every move.

data.name: Almudron Whisker
data.description: These crimson Almudron whiskers sense vibrations to help locate prey.

data.name: Almudron Whisker+
data.description: The longer the whiskers, the better they can sense vibration. Intruders beware.

data.name: Almudron Tail
data.description: An impressive Almudron tail. Its willow-esque droop opens up opportunities to strike.

data.name: Golden Muck
data.description: Mud mixed with Almudron mucus. Prized for its viscosity and sumptuous hue.

data.name: Golden Sludge
data.description: Mud with high levels of mucus. Coveted by smiths for its miraculous properties.

data.name: Almudron Plate
data.description: Rare Almudron scale. As you stare into its gray hue, you feel sucked in.

data.name: Golden Almudron Orb
data.description: The contrast of cloudy dull hues and brilliant gold in this jewel is one-of-a-kind.

data.name: Zinogre Shell
data.description: A blue-green shell which stores electricity and works as a protective insulator.

data.name: Zinogre Carapace
data.description: The carapace of a Zinogre. Its magnificence reveals the futility of facing it.

data.name: Zinogre Shockfur
data.description: White fur that stores and magnifies electricity, which it holds even after carving.

data.name: Zinogre Electrofur
data.description: Zinogre fur said to store lots of electricity. Shines white from the charge.

data.name: Zinogre Horn
data.description: The Zinogre's magnificent horn, which sends most of nature running for cover.

data.name: Zinogre Horn+
data.description: A pointed Zinogre horn. When carved, it grants equipment incomparable power.

data.name: Zinogre Claw
data.description: A sharp and tremendously powerful claw capable of quickly dicing up prey.

data.name: Zinogre Claw+
data.description: A high voltage Zinogre claw. Its electrified attacks are truly brutal.

data.name: Zinogre Tail
data.description: The plate-covered tail of a Zinogre. It wields deadly force when swung.

data.name: Zinogre Shocker
data.description: The ocher shell that once lined a Zinogre's body. Contains conductive lipids.

data.name: Zinogre Shocker+
data.description: An electrically charged Zinogre shell. Grants a thunder god's power to gear.

data.name: Fulgurbug
data.description: Thunderbugs which have been stimulated by Zinogre. They emit a pale blue light.

data.name: Zinogre Plate
data.description: A rare and intimidating trophy that seems to pulse with residual fury.

data.name: Zinogre Jasper
data.description: A rare gem sometimes produced inside a Zinogre's body. The beast's power swells within.

data.name: Tigrex Scale
data.description: Scale from the incredibly violent Tigrex. Incredibly massive and sturdy.

data.name: Tigrex Scale+
data.description: A flawless Tigrex scale. Can be fastened with others to become harder than steel.

data.name: Tigrex Shell
data.description: A hard Tigrex shell capable of repelling any impact. Extreme tenacity.

data.name: Tigrex Carapace
data.description: A material hardened by the sands of time. Sharp edges show the Tigrex's ferocity.

data.name: Tigrex Claw
data.description: A vicious foreclaw unique to the Tigrex. Known for its insidious biting edge.

data.name: Tigrex Claw+
data.description: A claw that time has sharpened into a horrible death sentence for prey.

data.name: Tigrex Fang
data.description: A terrifying fang used to crush prey. Makes all who see it quiver in fear.

data.name: Tigrex Fang+
data.description: The sharp fang of a Tigrex. These fangs can cut any prey to shreds.

data.name: Tigrex Tail
data.description: This flexible and strong tail can make great equipment.

data.name: Tigrex Scalp
data.description: Part of the head of a Tigrex. Looks terrifying, as if it is still alive.

data.name: Tigrex Maw
data.description: The awe-inspiring jaws of a Tigrex, ready to crush both bone and spirit.

data.name: Diablos Shell
data.description: Shell from a Diablos. It's incredibly dense, and much heavier than it looks.

data.name: Diablos Carapace
data.description: A quality Diablos carapace, buffed and hardened by constant exposure to sand.

data.name: Diablos Ridge
data.description: A rigid Diablos backplate. Can be carved into fine gear with the right knife skills.

data.name: Diablos Ridge+
data.description: A particularly thick, hard Diablos carapace. Sturdy, but a pain to carve off.

data.name: Diablos Tailcase
data.description: An armored tailcase that puts iron hammers to shame. This material is a keeper.

data.name: Diablos Fang
data.description: A large, sturdy fang used in everything from weapons to ornaments.

data.name: Twisted Horn
data.description: A twisted Diablos horn. Used in this region for many (less twisted) purposes.

data.name: Majestic Horn
data.description: A twisted Diablos horn in great shape. Use it to make more powerful weapons.

data.name: Diablos Marrow
data.description: Diablos bone marrow. Recently discovered to have superb binding properties.

data.name: Diablos Medulla
data.description: A rare medulla. Difficult to remove, but of great interest to researchers.

data.name: Rakna-Kadaki Silk
data.description: Quality Rakna-Kadaki silk. A garb woven from this silk is sure to cushion any blow.

data.name: Rakna-Kadaki Carapace
data.description: Hard, heavy Rakna-Kadaki carapace sometimes used in weapons and armor.

data.name: Rakna-Kadaki Sharpclaw
data.description: A Rakna-Kadaki claw. Capable of such a punch, it could shatter a dragon's hide.

data.name: Rakna-Kadaki Spike
data.description: A spike that has a charming curve. Used in weapons as well as for decoration.

data.name: Rakna-Kadaki Glowgut
data.description: A Rakna-Kadaki organ that glows alluringly, but burns with magmatic heat.

data.name: Daora Carapace
data.description: A shell hardened by time. Crafting with it is incredibly difficult.

data.name: Daora Dragon Scale+
data.description: High-quality scale from Kushala Daora. It is said to surpass steel.

data.name: Daora Webbing
data.description: A lightweight yet sturdy Kushala Daora wing. Shines a dull silver when polished.

data.name: Daora Horn+
data.description: A fierce-looking horn that instantly robs the body of cold if handled improperly.

data.name: Daora Tail
data.description: Cut from Kushala Daora. Incredibly destructive power contained within.

data.name: Daora Claw+
data.description: Even now the black gleam of this claw seems to emit a life force.

data.name: Daora Gem
data.description: A rare gem formed inside a Daora. Its glow is breathtaking.

data.name: Chameleos Hide+
data.description: Superior hide of a Chameleos. Strange to the touch, but very durable.

data.name: Chameleos Spike
data.description: A sharp horn of a Chameleos. Strong and hard, but strangely easy to work with.

data.name: Chameleos Claw+
data.description: Sharpened claw of a Chameleos. Small and sharp, but still valued for being easy to work with.

data.name: Chameleos Tail
data.description: The distinctive tail of Chameleos. Feels very strange.

data.name: Chameleos Wing
data.description: While this material is strong, the surface's weird texture is its highlight.

data.name: Chameleos Gem
data.description: A rare gem formed inside Chameleos. It has a multi-colored glow.

data.name: Teostra Carapace
data.description: Harder than Teostra Shell. Looks like red-hot steel; particularly eye catching.

data.name: Teostra Mane
data.description: This majestic mane is a sure sign of Teostra's regality.

data.name: Teostra Tail
data.description: Covered in red scales, the tree-like tail of Teostra is incredibly hard to cut.

data.name: Teostra Horn+
data.description: A sharp horn that burns with the fury of Teostra. It is tinged with fire.

data.name: Fire Dragon Scale+
data.description: Scale that seems to burn with the majesty of a fire dragon.

data.name: Teostra Claw+
data.description: The blow of this ever-hot claw awaits those who evade the fiery breath of Teostra.

data.name: Teostra Webbing
data.description: A Teostra wing that repels any flame. You sense strength and valor in it.

data.name: Teostra Powder
data.description: Powder from fire dragon wings. Said to magnify a material's abilities.

data.name: Teostra Gem
data.description: A rare gem formed inside a fire dragon. Flickers with ferocious flames.

data.name: Rajang Horn+
data.description: The majestic golden horn of a Rajang. Hunters yearn for the heroism it represents.

data.name: Rajang Fang+
data.description: This sharpened fang can cut through anything dumb enough to touch it.

data.name: Rajang Blackfur
data.description: Black Rajang fur. When crafted, the resulting cloth is desired even by royalty.

data.name: Rajang Claw+
data.description: A sharp Rajang claw. Difficult to carve and more difficult to craft.

data.name: Rajang Tail
data.description: The glistening tail of a Rajang. The golden fur is beautiful and elegant.

data.name: Gold Rajang Pelt
data.description: Fur taken from a Rajang's body. The golden hair is treasured by tailors.

data.name: Bazelgeuse Scale+
data.description: It appears that this would dampen violent impacts. Shines a dull silver.

data.name: Bazelgeuse Carapace
data.description: Strong enough to entirely ignore the harsh explosions of Bazelgeuse scales.

data.name: Bazelgeuse Tail
data.description: This tail is packed with explosive scales; each one could take out your house!

data.name: Bazelgeuse Fuse
data.description: Explosive fluid-producing organ. Drop it, and you'll be standing in a crater.

data.name: Bazelgeuse Talon
data.description: These massive honed claws are the incarnation of destructive force.

data.name: Bazelgeuse Wing
data.description: Massive wing developed to chase prey to the ends of the earth.

data.name: Bazelgeuse Gem
data.description: Those drawn in by this jewel's glow instantly snap into a maddened rage.

data.name: Ibushi Hide+
data.description: Rigid enough to repel blades yet flexible as rubber, this hide fends off all attacks.

data.name: Ibushi Carapace
data.description: Carapace of Ibushi. Oddly, the skin is hard, elastic, and also lightweight.

data.name: Ibushi Claw+
data.description: One swipe with this pointy claw disfigures the land with a gust-like blow.

data.name: Ibushi Horn+
data.description: Careful polishing could turn this horn into a graceful, gleaming azure blade.

data.name: Ibushi Windsac
data.description: Organ that stores and emits air. Inflates to float on self-created drafts.

data.name: Ibushi Bluespike
data.description: Countless rock-hard spikes prevent airborne enemies from getting close.

data.name: Wind Serpent Orb
data.description: This jewel shimmers with the rage of a typhoon. Its holder commands the storm.

data.name: Narwa Hide+
data.description: Hide so well insulated, it makes lightning strikes feel like bug bites.

data.name: Narwa Carapace
data.description: Flexible and lightweight carapace that courses with flesh-singeing electricity.

data.name: Narwa Claw+
data.description: A sharp claw that once sliced up any foolish enough to attack Narwa.

data.name: Narwa Horn+
data.description: Narwa's horn. Shoots out bolts of lightning when swung; handle with caution.

data.name: Narwa Sparksac
data.description: This lightning-emitting organ creates a magnetic field to enable floating.

data.name: Narwa Tentacle
data.description: Tentacles that cover Narwa's body. It uses them to shroud itself in lightning.

data.name: Thunder Serpent Orb
data.description: This jewel shimmers with the ire of lightning. Its holder can tame thunder.

data.name: Scale of Origin

data.name: Horn of Origin
data.description: This horn dominates gales dancing across the sky and earth-splitting thunder.

data.name: Orb of Origin
data.description: Within this jewel from the Allmother dance father wind and mother lightning.

data.name: Valstrax Tail

data.name: Rouge Spikewing

data.name: Valstrax Spineshell
data.description: A Valstrax shell used for back protection. Its sharp points look like blades.

data.name: Red Dragon Orb
data.description: The source of evil heavenly omens. Fly fleetly, as a comet 'cross the skies.

data.name: Crimson Liquid

data.description: You can see the beast's will to live from the scars this horn has endured.

data.name: Apex Shockshell
data.description: Battle-scarred carapace of an Apex Zinogre. Surges with electricity when disgraced.
